WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.471 --> 00:00:03.651
<v ->Pamela Cayton spent 10 years of her life in Nepal,</v>

2
00:00:03.651 --> 00:00:05.673
serving as a teacher in an orphanage.

3
00:00:05.673 --> 00:00:06.633
Little did she know

4
00:00:06.633 --> 00:00:09.231
that these children were going to forever change her life

5
00:00:09.231 --> 00:00:12.271
and her relationship to the field of education.

6
00:00:12.271 --> 00:00:13.711
Upon her return to the west,

7
00:00:13.711 --> 00:00:15.411
she settled in Silicon Valley,

8
00:00:15.411 --> 00:00:18.892
180 degrees off her previous experience.

9
00:00:18.892 --> 00:00:22.112
Shocked at the lack of genuine curiosity from the children

10
00:00:22.112 --> 00:00:23.812
and their sense of entitlement,

11
00:00:23.812 --> 00:00:26.372
she began to devise a new system of teaching

12
00:00:26.372 --> 00:00:28.412
called essential education,

13
00:00:28.412 --> 00:00:31.143
which allows children to learn through the understanding

14
00:00:31.143 --> 00:00:34.483
of the interconnectedness of all things.

